  "text": "There is one other study using ASL in AESD [CITATION_1] , which showed that reduced ASL signals in bilateral frontal lobes on day 1 predicted the development of AESD. However, that study probably observed only postictal hypoperfusion, as seen after the first SE in our case, and did not present ASL findings around day 4 just before the appearance of reduced subcortical diffusion.",
  "correct_citation": {
